# Micro-Demo: Pro-Code Plot

## Skills

Read and follow:
1. `~/.agents/skills/app-studio-pro-code/SKILL.md` — embedding flow, context API, card instances
2. `~/.agents/skills/publish/SKILL.md` — `domo publish` workflow
3. `~/.agents/skills/manifest/SKILL.md` — manifest configuration

## MANDATORY: Reference Chart Code

**Before writing any chart code, read the gold-standard reference at `reference-charts/overview-composed-chart/` in this workspace.** This is the proven, production-tested pattern. Every pro-code chart MUST match this quality level.

Read ALL THREE files as your starting point:
- `reference-charts/overview-composed-chart/app.js` — 339 lines, full ComposedChart
- `reference-charts/overview-composed-chart/app.css` — 279 lines, production styling
- `reference-charts/overview-composed-chart/index.html` — import map pattern

### What the reference chart includes (MANDATORY for Overview/main page):

1. **ComposedChart** with multiple data series:
   - Actual line: solid, dark color (`strokeWidth: 2`, `dot: false`)
   - Plan line: solid, brand color (`strokeWidth: 2`, `dot: false`)
   - Forecast line: **dashed** (`strokeDasharray: '4 3'`, `dot: false`)
   - Confidence band: `Area` with `linearGradient` fill (`confidenceRange: [lower, upper]`)

2. **Controls** (top-right of chart header):
   - Aggregation `<select>` dropdown: Daily / Weekly / Monthly
   - Confidence band toggle `<button>` with active/inactive state

3. **Chart elements**:
   - `CartesianGrid` with `vertical: false`, dashed horizontal lines
   - `XAxis` with `tickFormatter`, `tickLine: false`
   - `YAxis` with abbreviated numbers (`fmtNum`: K, M), no axis line, rotated label
   - `Tooltip` with custom component showing all series values
   - `ReferenceLine` for "Today" (dashed vertical, labeled)

4. **Footer legend** (manual, NOT Recharts built-in):
   - Solid line swatch + "Actual"
   - Solid line swatch + "Plan"
   - Dashed line swatch + "Forecast" (uses `repeating-linear-gradient` in CSS)
   - Gradient box swatch + "Confidence Band" (only when toggle is active)

5. **Data handling**:
   - `parseData()` handles both array-of-arrays and object formats
   - `aggregateData()` properly sums across day/week/month periods
   - `fetchData()` checks `isDomoEnvironment()` and uses `domo.get('/data/v1/{alias}')`

6. **States**: Loading (animated 3×3 grid), Error (styled message)

### Adapting for sub-pages (Production, Quality, Supply Chain):

- **Bar charts**: Use `BarChart` or horizontal `BarChart` with `layout='vertical'`
- **Multi-line**: Use `ComposedChart` with 2–3 `Line` components (different colors, no Area/bands)
- **All sub-page charts** still need: aggregation toggle, custom tooltip, footer legend, loading/error states
- **Each page's chart MUST look visually distinct** — different chart type, different dataset, different column

## Demo Pack

Read `demo-packs/{vertical}.md` for chart type assignments and dataset-to-page mappings.

## Input Requirements

- Target App Studio appId and pageId(s)
- Dataset GUIDs for chart data
- Source: conversation context, or ask

## Procedure

1. Read the reference chart code at `reference-charts/overview-composed-chart/`
2. Read demo pack for chart type per page
3. For each page, create an app directory by **copying and adapting** the reference code:
   - `index.html` — use reference as-is (ryuu.js + import map)
   - `app.css` — start from reference CSS, change colors to match palette
   - `app.js` — start from reference JS, change: DATASET_ALIAS, column names, COLORS object, chart title/subtitle, chart type (ComposedChart vs BarChart)
   - `manifest.json` — `datasetsMapping` with correct GUID, alias, `fields: []`
   - `thumbnail.png` — 300×300 solid color PNG (REQUIRED or publish fails DA0087)
4. Publish: `cd {app-dir} && domo publish` → record designId
5. Create context: `POST https://modocorp.domo.com/domoapps/apps/v2/contexts` (ROOT DOMAIN, not /api/)
6. Create card: `POST https://modocorp.domo.com/domoapps/apps/v2?fullpage=false&pageId={pageId}`
7. Place in layout: width 60, height 30, style ca1, fitToFrame true

## Output Contract

Report: designId, cardId, placement coordinates, page it was added to.

## Critical Rules

- **Overview page MUST use ComposedChart** with Actual + Plan + Forecast + Confidence Band (if data supports it)
- **Different chart type per sub-page** — never repeat the same type across pages
- **Start from reference code, then adapt** — never write chart code from scratch
- **Alias chain must match**: manifest `alias` = context mapping `alias` = `domo.get('/data/v1/{alias}')` in app.js
- **Context API uses ROOT DOMAIN** (`https://modocorp.domo.com/domoapps/...`), NOT `/api/domoapps/...`
- **Wrap `domo.onFiltersUpdated` in try-catch** — prevents blank chart crash
- **Colors are HARDCODED** — pro-code iframes do NOT inherit the App Studio theme
- **No build step** — static HTML app, publish directly with `domo publish`
- **Each app directory needs its OWN manifest.json** with the CORRECT dataset GUID and alias
- **Include `thumbnail.png`** or publish fails with DA0087
